  "text": "The error string 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates from the authoritative etcd-io/etcd repository, NOT from vendored copies in kubernetes/kubernetes. There are two key locations: First, the ErrCompacted error variable is defined in server/mvcc/kvstore.go (line 39) as: var ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\"). This is the authoritative error definition. Second, the core function rangeKeys in server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (starting at line 128) is responsible for returning this error when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction. Specifically, at lines 136-137, the rangeKeys function checks: if rev < tr.s.compactMainRev { return &RangeResult{KVs: nil, Count: -1, Rev: 0}, ErrCompacted }. This check detects when the requested revision is less than the compactMainRev, indicating that the requested revision has been compacted, and returns the ErrCompacted error. These are the authoritative source locations in etcd-io/etcd v3.5.17. The kubernetes/kubernetes repository contains vendored copies of etcd code under vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/, but those are not the authoritative source. Additionally, kubernetes/kubernetes has its own error-mapping layer at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go that wraps this error into Kubernetes error types, but this is also not the authoritative source of the original error definition."
}

